abstract: Digital mapping company HERE Technologies sold a 30% stake to Mitsubishi Corp and Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp (NTT), diluting German carmakers' stake to 54% amid uncertainty about the profit potential from autonomous cars.
snippet: Digital mapping company HERE Technologies sold a 30% stake to Mitsubishi Corp and Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp (NTT), diluting German carmakers' stake to 54% amid uncertainty about the profit potential from autonomous cars.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Digital mapping company HERE Technologies sold a 30% stake to Mitsubishi Corp and Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp (NTT), diluting German carmakers' stake to 54% amid uncertainty about the profit potential from autonomous cars.
headline_main: Mitsubishi, NTT to Buy 30% Stake in Digital Mapping Company HERE
headline_print_headline: Mitsubishi, NTT to Buy 30% Stake in Digital Mapping Company HERE

abstract: More than a week after a 33-year-old Texas mother and her infant daughter vanished, authorities said Friday they found the woman dead more than 100 miles (160.93 kilometers) away but the baby safe, and have charged a suspect with kidnapping and tampering with a corpse.
snippet: More than a week after a 33-year-old Texas mother and her infant daughter vanished, authorities said Friday they found the woman dead more than 100 miles (160.93 kilometers) away but the baby safe, and have charged a suspect with kidnapping and ta...
lead_paragraph: AUSTIN, Texas — More than a week after a 33-year-old Texas mother and her infant daughter vanished, authorities said Friday they found the woman dead more than 100 miles (160.93 kilometers) away but the baby safe, and have charged a suspect with kidnapping and tampering with a corpse.
headline_main: Police Say Texas Mother Found Dead Was Strangled, Baby Safe
headline_print_headline: Police Say Texas Mother Found Dead Was Strangled, Baby Safe

abstract: Wall Street analysts were upbeat about Nike Inc's long-term growth, encouraged by the sportswear maker's robust online sales and strength in China that helped overcome slowing demand in North America, its biggest market.
snippet: Wall Street analysts were upbeat about Nike Inc's long-term growth, encouraged by the sportswear maker's robust online sales and strength in China that helped overcome slowing demand in North America, its biggest market.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Wall Street analysts were upbeat about Nike Inc's long-term growth, encouraged by the sportswear maker's robust online sales and strength in China that helped overcome slowing demand in North America, its biggest market.
headline_main: Wall Street Analysts Bullish Over Nike's Digital Growth, Look Past Margin Weakness
headline_print_headline: Wall Street Analysts Bullish Over Nike's Digital Growth, Look Past Margin Weakness

abstract: The USMCA North American trade deal will bring jobs, technology and investment to Mexico, Foreign Minister Marcelo Ebrard said on Friday, a day after the agreement passed a major hurdle and was approved in the U.S. House of Representatives.
snippet: The USMCA North American trade deal will bring jobs, technology and investment to Mexico, Foreign Minister Marcelo Ebrard said on Friday, a day after the agreement passed a major hurdle and was approved in the U.S. House of Representatives.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — The USMCA North American trade deal will bring jobs, technology and investment to Mexico, Foreign Minister Marcelo Ebrard said on Friday, a day after the agreement passed a major hurdle and was approved in the U.S. House of Representatives.
headline_main: Jobs, Tech and Investment for Mexico, Government Celebrates USMCA Deal
headline_print_headline: Jobs, Tech and Investment for Mexico, Government Celebrates USMCA Deal

abstract: Estonians have always headed to the forests in their thousands to cut down Christmas trees, but these days they will probably have a smartphone in their hands.

abstract: Global equity funds attracted $14.8 billion (£11.36 billion) last week, Bank of America Global said on Friday, as investors stormed back to risky assets after U.S.-China agreed on a trade truce and a clear majority in the UK election cleared Brexit fog.
snippet: Global equity funds attracted $14.8 billion (£11.36 billion) last week, Bank of America Global said on Friday, as investors stormed back to risky assets after U.S.-China agreed on a trade truce and a clear majority in the UK election cleared Brexi...
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Global equity funds attracted $14.8 billion (£11.36 billion) last week, Bank of America Global said on Friday, as investors stormed back to risky assets after U.S.-China agreed on a trade truce and a clear majority in the UK election cleared Brexit fog.
headline_main: Global Equity Funds Suck in $15 Billion in Brexit, Trade Truce Week-BofA

abstract: The German economy probably shrank in the fourth quarter as export-oriented manufacturing continued to decline, the DIW economic institute said on Friday.
snippet: The German economy probably shrank in the fourth quarter as export-oriented manufacturing continued to decline, the DIW economic institute said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — The German economy probably shrank in the fourth quarter as export-oriented manufacturing continued to decline, the DIW economic institute said on Friday.
headline_main: German Economy Likely to Contract in Fourth Quarter, DIW Says
headline_print_headline: German Economy Likely to Contract in Fourth Quarter, DIW Says

abstract: Anne Sacoolas, the wife of an American diplomat, was accused of killing the teenage motorcyclist when driving on the wrong side of the road in central England in August.
snippet: Anne Sacoolas, the wife of an American diplomat, was accused of killing the teenage motorcyclist when driving on the wrong side of the road in central England in August.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — An American woman who fled Britain after her car collided with a teenage motorcyclist in central England in August while she was driving on the wrong side of the road has been charged with causing death by dangerous driving, British prosecutors said on Friday.

snippet: “I I I I I I I I I I I I I I I hhhave absolutely no idea what Biden is talking about,” Ms. Sanders tweeted during the Democratic presidential debate. She later deleted the post and apologized.
lead_paragraph: Sarah Huckabee Sanders apologized late Thursday after she mocked comments by former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. during the Democratic presidential debate in which he recounted mentoring a boy who had a speech impediment.
